race.comment: DUNDEEL FLYER (9) is in a top Sydney stable and is well-placed to win. She peaks off strong runs at provincial and metro level and Alysha is a key jockey engagement. She still has more to give and maps for a soft run in transit. Next best is the local ROONAMI (14), who missed a whisker here first-up. Penza has to manage a wide gate, but the filly has plenty of scope for improvement and is likely to come hard. BRUTAL BELLE (5) was heavily backed when missing a lip at Moruya, but was plain after at Cootamundra when expected to win (vet cleared). She will use an inside barrier and can bounce into the placings. GLASTONBURY GIRL (11) raced new at Kembla Grange on debut and found a place in a Warwick Farm trial since. Likely needs more time but she's in good hands and goes into the trifectas/first fours.
